pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.1.0-6) unstable; urgency=medium

  * UI overhaul on the Label tab: soft Qt-rendered preview by default (smooth,
    anti-aliased) with an "Exact (pixel-accurate)" toggle that falls back to
    ptouch-print --writepng for the printer-accurate rendering.
  * Preview now has a zoom selector (100% / 200% / 300% / 400% / 600% / 800%)
    instead of always upscaling to canvas width — fixes the giant pixellated
    look. Background switched to light "tape" off-white with a thin border.
  * Status pill at top of Label tab: live ● Printer / tape width / ready
    indicator so device state is visible without tab-switching.
  * Format + Print options consolidated into one tighter group. Print button
    is now the primary accent-coloured action. "ptouch-print output" log
    collapsed behind a disclosure toggle.
  * Printer and Tape tabs merged into a single "Device" tab.
  * New "Batch" tab: queue rows of (text, copies); buttons for new row,
    duplicate, delete, clear, save manifest, import manifest (JSON).
    Threaded run with progress bar and cancel. Format settings come from
    the Label tab so the whole batch shares font/cut/etc.
  * Added 9 Hebrew Google Fonts: Heebo, Assistant, Noto Sans Hebrew, Noto
    Serif Hebrew, Frank Ruhl Libre, David Libre, Suez One, Secular One,
    Miriam Libre, Bellefair.
  * Automatic RTL layout: when a Hebrew-category font is selected or when
    Hebrew characters are typed, the text input flips to right-aligned RTL
    and the soft preview uses Qt's bidi-aware text layout. Preview meta
    line shows "· RTL" when active.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Mon, 18 May 2026 22:55:00 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.1.0-5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: font-installed detection was always returning false, so every font
    appeared "missing" in the Fonts tab even after a successful install.
    Root cause: was calling `fc-list :family` which returns lines like
    "/path/to/x.ttf: Lato:style=Regular" — the path prefix was being parsed
    as part of the family name. Switched to
    `fc-list -f '%{family}\n'` which emits one bare family per line.
    The downloads were always working; only the UI status was wrong.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Mon, 18 May 2026 23:50:00 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.1.0-4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fonts now install into ~/.local/share/fonts/google-fonts/ — the standard
    XDG user font directory, visible to every desktop app for this user.
    Previously installed into an app-private subfolder which behaved like a
    private cache.
  * Added one-shot migration on app startup: any TTFs left over in the old
    ~/.local/share/fonts/pt-p710bt-label-gui/ are moved into the new
    location and fontconfig is refreshed. Status-bar message confirms.
  * Replaced "maintained" wording throughout (banned-word rule).

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Mon, 18 May 2026 23:30:00 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.1.0-3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Restructured the GUI into tabs (was: single overloaded window).
    - Label tab: text input, format, options, image, live preview, Print.
    - Printer tab: connection status, dpi, max width, raw --info dump.
    - Tape tab: width / usable px / media / colours / error byte, all on
      their own surface with explanatory note.
    - Fonts tab: top-level — replaces the buried Tools menu. Maintained font
      table with installed/missing badges, "Install missing" /
      "Reinstall all" buttons, threaded progress + log.
  * Label tab font row now has a "Manage…" button that jumps to the
    Fonts tab — the install path is two clicks from anywhere.
  * Dropped the modal font installer dialog (FontInstallDialog) and the
    Tools menu — superseded by the Fonts tab.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Mon, 18 May 2026 23:00:00 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.1.0-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Maintained Google Fonts library (30 fonts incl. Heebo for Hebrew).
    - Font picker is now a category-grouped dropdown sourced from
      pt_p710bt_label_gui.fonts; default is IBM Plex Sans.
    - Each entry tagged "(not installed)" when fontconfig doesn't see it.
  * New Tools menu → "Install Google Fonts…" dialog.
    - Lists every maintained font with installed/missing status.
    - "Install missing" and "Reinstall all" buttons; threaded download +
      progress log; runs fc-cache when done.
    - Downloads directly from github.com/google/fonts (canonical source) —
      no third-party mirror, no API key required.
  * Replaced "Chain" checkbox with "Auto-cut after print" (default ON).
    When OFF, ptouch-print is invoked with --chain.

